From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 09:15:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] katirun: drive per-instance make inputs from a local Flags,
 not global FLAGS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Prerequisite for an in-process `make` builtin. kati's FLAGS is a global
LazyLock installed once via install_args (an OnceLock); a second make in the
same process would fail to re-install and would share one config. Split the
two roles:

- The immutable mode-switches stay in the global FLAGS. install_args is now
  best-effort (a repeated install in the same process is tolerated, not a
  fatal "already initialized" error) since the switches are identical.
- The per-instance INPUTS — makefile, targets, cl_vars (and the makefile
  default-discovery / missing-file error) — now come from a LOCAL
  kati::flags::Flags::from_args(kargv) (made pub) instead of reading the
  global. run_kati takes the makefile as a parameter and no longer reads
  FLAGS.makefile.

For the existing shadow/main() path (one make per process) the local Flags is
parsed from the same synthesized argv as the global, so behavior is identical:
corpus KATI_COMPAT_PASS=364/378, fail=0; engine builds. This unblocks multiple
make invocations coexisting in one process without colliding on inputs.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01XyA6FzC6QGgsrjEYEBJV46
---
 src-rs/flags.rs | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src-rs/flags.rs b/src-rs/flags.rs
index 1235ec3..dc56b82 100644
--- a/src-rs/flags.rs
+++ b/src-rs/flags.rs
@@ -138,7 +138,13 @@ fn parse_command_line_option_with_arg(
 }
 
 impl Flags {
-    fn from_args(args: Vec<OsString>) -> Flags {
+    /// sarun: pub so an embedder can parse a per-instance Flags from a
+    /// synthesized argv instead of relying solely on the install-once global
+    /// FLAGS — needed when multiple make invocations share one process (the
+    /// in-process `make` builtin). The global FLAGS still supplies the
+    /// immutable mode-switches; per-instance INPUTS (makefile/targets/cl_vars/
+    /// working_dir) come from a local Flags so concurrent makes don't collide.
+    pub fn from_args(args: Vec<OsString>) -> Flags {
         let mut iter = args.into_iter();
         let mut flags = Flags::default();
         flags.subkati_args.push(iter.next().unwrap());
